tion-state but also challenged the authority of the central state. As a result, Basque region-building reveals the strengths and weaknesses of the unitary model of French nationhood, in the nineteenth century as well as today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aFolklorezFrancezPays Basque. 0aRegionalismzFrancey19th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh  aAugustin Chaho.  aBertsolaritza.  aFirst Carlist War.  aFrench Basque country.  aFrench Revolution.  aNapoleonic Wars.  anationalism.  aphilology.  aregionalism.  atourism.  atourist gaze.  atravel writing.1 aIlacqua, Talitha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2024 eBook-Packagez9783111332345oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152616926640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526169266423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526169266/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPb2024